    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family containing 11 species in four genera including skunks and stink badgers, having moderately elongated bodies with reasonably short well-muscled legs, long front claws for digging, a striped coat, and extremely well-developed anal scent glands used to produce noxious odors to deter threats.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
